cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a method to dissect and reconstruct convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique used in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves interpretability analyses, which falls under the category of explainable AI (cs.AI). The use of specific parts of a CNN for specific tasks also relates to neural architecture search (cs.NE). Finally, the paper's focus on applying CNNs with given knowledge could also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
